sentences: Cheri Dennis (born August 7, 1979), is an American R&B singer from Cleveland, Ohio.
Dennis first appeared on the Mase tracks "No Matter What", "All I Ever Wanted" and "If You Want to Party" from his album Double Up (1999), after running into Diddy during a party in New York City.

The music video was filmed in March 2006 before premiering on BET's 106 & Park on May 1.
Dennis' second single "Portrait of Love" peaked at No. 55 before her debut album In and Out of Love finally released in February 2008, debuting at No. 74 on the Billboard 200.
